# Author identity unification.
# Maps historical author name/email pairs to a canonical identity so
# `git shortlog`, `git log --use-mailmap`, and GitHub contributor stats
# display one entry per person. History on disk is preserved as-is.
#
# Format: Canonical Name <canonical-email> Commit Name <commit-email>
# See `man gitmailmap` for the full grammar.

itsoneohone <itsoneohone@proton.me> oneohone <itsoneohone@proton.me>
itsoneohone <itsoneohone@proton.me> itsoneohone <138209743+itsoneohone@users.noreply.github.com>
